data.title: Good food, slow service
data.text: We arrived around 10:30 on a Sunday morning and weren't expecting there to be a long wait, but did have to wait about 20 minutes for a table. We had requested a booth since we had a two year old granddaughter and a 9 month pregnant daughter with us, but were seated at a table anyway.  We took what we got due to avoid a longer wait.  As soon as our server arrived we put in the order for the funny face pancakes for our granddaughter.  Her food still did not arrive for another 20 minutes.  Our food came out probably 15 minutes after that.  Probably the slowest service we have ever had at any IHOP.  Food is always good and employees very nice but just too slow this time.

data.title: Angie's visit to Montgomery Village
data.text: I believe it's the only place in this area open after 9:00 to accommodate a crowd of 15 or more. Everyone was happy with the food and despite of having just one server at this time, she did An awesome job of serving, splitting bills and still remain friendly.

data.title: Good service by server
data.text:
We were there for mothers day breakfast. We arrived before 9 am and were seated immediately. The server -Dalia p- was excellent. She took our order fast, and checked on us many times while we were dining. 
I gave 4 starts just because we received our food very late. I know it was mothers day and Sunday is usually busy day, but you still expect to receive your food in a timely manner.
I was also with 2 kids ages 1 and 4. My little one did not want to stay and he was keep crying and it made me frustrated. I could not eat until an hour later! 
That made me very upset and I did not smiled nor made eye contact when Dalia was trying to check on us couple times. Still she managed to take care of us and provide excellent service. she was really impressive and patient.

data.title: Good food served quickly at a good price
data.text: Went for lunch on a Saturday afternoon. Restaurant was busy but not crowded. I was seated immediately and had my order taken right away. I ordered the 2 egg breakfast which was served very quickly and was exactly what I wanted. I ordered a side of grits which was a large serving, but was also quite nice. I was in and out in 30 minutes with the comfort food I was seeking in between.

data.title: Ate here many times and never disappointed
data.text: The same IHOP around but this one is the one I like the most. I believe it's the management. The service is always good and fast. The food is in good consistent quality.

data.title: Bad experience
data.text: my friend and I went here this past winter around new years we got there were seated given a menu the waiter came over took our drink order and I don't know what happened I guess he forgot about us we stayed for about 10 minutes and then left very dissatisfied will not come again it's a shame because I usually like their pancakes

data.title: Good Representation of the IHOP Chain
data.text:
We had visited the IHOP in Gaithersberg while on vacation. There was quite a wait to sit, but the had plenty of seating available for waiting.

Service was fast and friendly. Both of our breakfasts came out quick and tasted very good.  Our server checked on us regularly the whole time.  

The IHOP is fairly representative of many of the well run IHOPs in the nation. Service and food are both good, and I would have no hesitation in visiting again....

data.title: They know the business
data.text: I've been going to this iHOP forever. Service has always been excellent, even when there were 30 rowdy teenagers, food is consistently good, and you know what you're getting, 'cause it's an iHOP. Love that it's 24 hours, I always know where to go late.

data.title: Consistently good, excellent service, excellent food
data.text: Enjoyed a very breakfast recently at this IHOP outlet. The blueberry pancakes were outstanding. My wife's eggs cooked to perfection. Our service was friendly and quick and the coffee hot. We very much enjoyed our experience. The over 55 menu was appreciated and perfect for my wife and her mother.

data.title: Great Service!!!! Great Experience!!!
data.text: We love this IHOP!!!! The staff is exceptionally friendly and efficient. I have encouraged many of my friends and family to dine here.

data.title: Family breakfast
data.text: The restaurant was very busy.  Waitress was very friendly and kept our drinks full and delivered our food hot.  Food tasted great.  Only complaint was too much sun coming through door next to were we sat made it hard to see at times.

data.title: Go early
data.text:
It gets crowded on the weekends at 8:45 am, so go early or expect to wait.  
Stay simple and you'll leave happy.  I've order ambitious items like the Mediteranian Omelate and was disappointed, but when I've ordered signiture dishes or standards, I've been very happy.
Steer the kids to the kid's menu - a much better deal than ala carte'.  If you stay with the standard offerings, you'll get a good meal at a good price.  Add-ons are expensive.

data.title: I HOP Gaithersburg, MD
data.text: I am a veteran and went for the free Veterans Day menu item.  I was treated the same as any other customer even though I was getting a free meal.  The waitress was very friendly and courteous as the waitresses here always are.  Management knows how to provide great service and pretty good food.

data.title: Good, filling breakfast, smooth coffee
data.text: Tasty ham and poched eggs with toast which kept me full till lunch.  My hubby liked the pancakes, eggs, ham and home fries.  We intend to go back another time for lunch.

data.title: IHOP in Gaithersburg
data.text: We visit at least once per week. I am hooked on the omelettes and my wife loves the grain pancakes. the best

data.title: Breakfast for a Late Dinner
data.text: We stopped in for a late dinner.  The staff was warm and friendly.  We had the chocolate chip pancakes and the pancakes with strawberries and bananas.  It was comfort food that hit the spot.

data.title: Typical fare; Felt rushed to leave.
data.text: We called in for a reservation because it was pretty busy on a Sunday morning/afternoon. Making a reservation helps a bit. we were seated and the hostess was kind. The food took awhile to get to us, which is something that can be improved. The food was typical fare. One thing that I've noticed at IHOP (not just this one) is that they really do try to get you to leave early before you've finished your food. They will give you the bill, while you are eating, and say this is just for your convenience and please take your time. Their actions betray their words. I'm not just picking on this branch but every time I've been to IHOP this year (3x) this has happened. It must be the way they are trained. That is my gripe with IHOP. Anyway, the food was typical. So I'll give it three stars.

data.title: IHOP in Gaithersburg
data.text: We go here at least once a week for breakfast for dinner. Great food and service. great value for your money especially on senior night(monday)

data.title: Great for Breakfast
data.text: Short walk from hotel.  Staff very friendly and food was good.  We ate breakfast there 3 out of 5 days we stayed.

data.title: IHOP
data.text: Waitress was nice; pancakes were a little rubbery and colffee was luke warm; why do all the syrups at IHOP have musty smell? At least I had coupn for free pancakes.
